381	    % ── W = W1 * W2, unit Frobenius norm (||W||_F = 1) ───────────────────
382	    % Per TS 38.214 §5.2.2.2.5: W2 normalized s.t. ||W||_F=1 → total TX
383	    % power = 1, consistent with Approach B (sum log2(1+sv²/(r*nVar)))
384	    % and nrPMIReport output for Approach C/D.
385	    W = W1 * W2;
386	    W_fro = norm(W, 'fro');
